      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Small field with a handful of chances. TUSCANY (8) resumes from a lengthy spell and gelded over the break. Ran a narrow fourth to Attica last time in and looks primed for this with the two trials. Hard to hold out. NEWY (6) showed ability in his first campaign and expected to have strengthened over the break. Returns with the two trials and expected to figure in the finish. ANY QUESTIONS (2) faded badly in the heavy (9) going when fourth over 1200m at Kembla Grange in a Super Maiden third-up. Well drawn and has claims. DON'T WHAT ME (3) has been readied for the return with some nice trials and could be an improver this time around.",
